Title : John J. Abel Award
Text : {{refimprove|date=May 2014}}

The '''John J. Abel Award''' is an annual award presented by the [[American Society for Pharmacology and Experimental Therapeutics]] (ASPET). The award is given for outstanding research in the field of pharmacology and/or experimental therapeutics; which comes with a $5000 prize, An engraved plaque, and all travel expenses paid to attend the ASPET Annual Meeting at Experimental Biology. <ref>http://www.aspet.org/awards/aspet/abel/</ref>The Award is named after American [[biochemist]] and [[pharmacologist]], [[John Jacob Abel]].

